The northwest is vast and sparsely populated. To what extent is it rare? A large village has no more than a hundred families. So many families, a lot of brick houses. Much of the land, though plentiful, is unsuitable for cultivation. The villagers raise more livestock.



It was Now February and as cold as winter. Behind the village there were mountains bare and still visible with unmelted snow.
